description:
LAKERS at NUGGETS | FULL GAME HIGHLIGHTS | September 22, 2020

Led by Jamal Murray’s 28 PTS, 8 REB and 12 AST, the Denver Nuggets defeated the Los Angeles Lakers, 114-106, in Game 3. Additionally for the Nuggets, Nikola Jokic added 22 PTS, 10 REB and 5 AST in the victory, while LeBron James tallied 30 PTS, 10 REB and 11 AST for the Lakers, his 26th career playoff triple-double. The Lakers lead this best-of-seven series, 2-1.

Game 4: Thursday, September 24 at 9:00pm/et on TNT
